==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guna
<hw>Gu"na</hw> <pr>(g⟦oomac⟧"n⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>guna</ets> quality.]</ety> <def>In Sanskrit grammar, a lengthening
of the simple vowels <it>a</it>, <it>i</it>, <it>e</it>, by prefixing an
<it>a</it> element. The term is sometimes used to denote the same vowel
change in other languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gunarchy</ent>⟦br⟧
